"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-11-Li-Fabin-Ou-Zixia-to-bear-China-s-flag-at-Paris-2024-Closing-Ceremony-1vYIxu6n7Ik-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Sports Scene  Copied  Li Fabin (L) and Ou Zixia have been chosen as China's co-flagbearers for the Closing Ceremony of the 2024 Summer Olympics, in Paris, France, August 11, 2024. /CGTN  Li Fabin and Ou Zixia have been chosen as China's co-flagbearers for the Closing Ceremony of the 2024 Paris Summer Olympics on Sunday, the Chinese Olympic Committee announced.  Li, 31, won the men's 61-kilogram weightlifting gold medal on Wednesday to claim his second straight title, after previously topping the podium in the same division at the pandemic-delayed Tokyo Games in 2021.  Ou is a member of the Chinese women's field hockey team that earned silver in Paris after facing the Netherlands in the final on Friday. The second-place showing matched China's best finish in the sport, after the team previously bowed out as runners up at the 2008 Beijing Summer Olympics.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"